<div class="container px-5">
  <div class="jumbotron vertical-center my-5 py-5">
    <div class="container text-center">
      <h1 class="display-4">Peer Evaluation</h1>
      <%if !current_student && !current_professor %>
        <p class="lead">Login or join as a student or professor</p>
        <button type="button" class="btn btn-secondary btn-lg" onclick="window.location.href='/students/sign_in'">Student</button>
        <button type="button" class="btn btn-secondary btn-lg" onclick="window.location.href='/professors/sign_in'">Professor</button>
      <%else%>
        <p class="lead">Welcome!</p>
      <%end%>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
<br/>
<div class="container-fluid jumbotron mt-4" id="footer">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col">
        <h4 class="text-center text-secondary">What is Peer Evaluation?</h4>
        <br/>
        <p class="text-secondary">Peer Evaluation is just what it sounds like, a tool to help university instructors and students complete
          evaluations of their peers for group projects and presentations</p>
      </div>
      <div class="col">
        <h4 class="text-center text-secondary">Who can use Peer Evaluation?</h4>
        <br/>
        <p class="text-secondary">Peer Evaluation is free to use by anyone, but is built for student and instructors in a university setting,
        but we hope to include additional features in the future to make this tool accessible to more environments outside
        of academia.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="col">
        <h4 class="text-center text-secondary">How do I sign up?</h4>
        <br/>
        <p class="text-secondary">It's very simple and secure to sign up with Peer Evaluation. Simply click a prompt above to sign up as a student
          or professor. Just follow the <em>"sign-up"</em> link on the sign in page to create a new user account!</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
